-- Djokovic Takes Third Set of French Open Final, Trails Nadal 2-1
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 2012-06-10T16:36:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-10/djokovic-takes-third-set-of-french-open-final-trails-nadal-2-1.html
Top-seeded Novak Djokovic won the
third set of the French Open men’s tennis final, and trails six-
time champion Rafael Nadal 2-1 going into the fourth set.  Defending champion Nadal leads 6-4, 6-3, 2-6. It’s the
first set the Spaniard has lost this year at  Roland Garros . The
Serb is trying to win his four major tennis title in a row after
victories in Australia, the U.S. and Wimbledon.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  